  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: f1c4ed39d81c6554eb0788268ace8990, type: 3}
  m_Name: Customer7
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::DialogueData
  lines:
  - speakerName: Customer 7
    text: Hey doc. You ain't gonna believe this one. So I was walkin in the woods
      down by old Martha's cow farm, and I saw Martha out sittin on her stoop and
      you know she can chat like no other, and I hate chatting. Just really despise
      it. There's nothing more annoying than someone who just chats your ear off
      and won't get to the darn point. So naturally, I dove into the creek behind
      the field and let it carry me downstream till I was well out of social distance,
      and as I crawled out of the stream I was absolutely starving, I'd been floating
      for a good long while see, and there I saw the delicious bounty of the forest,
      so naturally being one of great affinity with the natural world I partook with
      the faith that the woods would nourish me. However, as I began to travel back,
      I was beset by vicious fairies! They stung and stabbed me with their needles
      till I ran all the way back here! Ever since, I've been dreadfully swollen
      and itchy! Think you can help?
    portrait: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 50f00414ad6290849a4f40f3ad20881f, type: 3}
    autoAdvanceDelay: 2
